			<tr><td colspan="2"><hr /></td></tr>
			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				(Cut & paste from an earlier post of mine:)
<br />

<br />
This is good, and I think that as my initial impression as a knight, yes even tho it doesn't benefit me directly, much. The important thing is that SoE is making a commitment to keep the game balanced. It seems to me that this method of balancing melee is a lot more friendly to tweaking than the current methods of melee balance... ie weapons and armor that may or may not be available to everyone based on their guild progression. 
<br />

<br />
This on the other hand will be easily changable... if something is overpowered, an easy change is made... underpowered and the same thing. Its not at all like an overpowered piece of armor or weapon or even spell that should never have been put into the game in the first place, which has been the bane of keeping class balance for these past 4 years. 
<br />

<br />
I also really like that people must time their shots. That will seperate the afkers from the people who play hard. As a SHD, I've always had to pay attention all the time to reach my potential (outside of Vex Thal anyways)... between tanking or just chaining spells for added DPS while walking the line of too much aggro or running out of mana too early (or not soon enough). Melee are now getting what they asked for, but its not a free lunch. You have to be alert and play with skill. That is a lot better than a mudflationary sweep of the hand as they've "fixed" things in the past.
<br />

<br />
So I like the idea a lot... now, to borrow a football-ism SoE just has to execute their play call.  And its all in the execution that will determine if this really fixes anything.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
	</tr>
